title: Bush Defends Brother Against Trump's 9/11 Criticism
text: Privacy Policy | More Newsletters AP Republican presidential candidate, former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush announces his plan to end President Obama's health care law, Tuesday, Oct. 13, 2015, at the New Hampshire Institute of Politics at Saint Anselm College in Manchester, N.H. After Donald Trump criticized former President George W. Bush over 9/11 attacks, Jeb Bush went to Twitter to call the comments "pathetic." How pathetic for @realdonaldtrump to criticize the president for 9/11. We were attacked & my brother kept us safe. â€” Jeb Bush (@JebBush) October 16, 2015 "When you talk about George Bush, I mean, say what you want, the World Trade Center came down during his time," Trump said in an interview Friday with Bloomberg. "He was president, OK? Blame him or don't blame him, but he was president. The World Trade Center came down during his reign." Nevada Shuts Down Daily Fantasy Sports Sites Earlier Friday, Jeb Bush told CBS news that no body knows what Trump's view of leader are because all he does is "talk about himself." While Bush regularly defends George W. Bush and appreciates his help in fundraising, Jeb Bush's key strategy in his campaign is to differentiate himself from his brother and his father.
